{"id":979,"date":"2023-07-24T08:00:23","date_gmt":"2023-07-24T15:00:23","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/imabi.org\/?page_id=979"},"modified":"2025-06-27T11:03:05","modified_gmt":"2025-06-27T18:03:05","slug":"adverbs-for-especially","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/imabi.org\/adverbs-for-especially\/","title":{"rendered":"Adverbs for &#8220;Especially&#8221;"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Adverbs for &#8220;Especially&#8221;: \u6b8a\u306b, \u7279\u306b,&nbsp;\u5c31\u4e2d, \u3068\u308a\u308f\u3051, \u6b8a\u66f4, etc.<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This lesson focuses on an array of interrelated adverbs which translate to &#8220;especially\/particularly.&#8221; Although some words may already be very familiar to you, others will be crucial additions to your vocabulary in preparation for the higher levels of the JLPT.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">\u6b8a\u306b<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The adverb \u6b8a\u306b derives from the adjectival noun&nbsp;\u7570\u306a\u308a meaning &#8220;to be different,&#8221; which you&#8217;ll recognize from the verb \u7570\u306a\u308b with the same meaning of &#8220;to be different.&#8221; In fact, \u7570\u306a\u308b is the verbalized form of \u7570\u306a\u308a.<br>&nbsp;<br>It should come as no surprise, then, that \u6b8a\u306b means that something &#8220;especially\/particularly&#8221; different. It is used to mark a higher degree of some quality in comparison to other things. This word is rather literary and is not heard too often in the spoken language.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>1. \u5929\u6587\u306f\u6b8a\u306b\u8239\u4e57\u308a\u306b\u5fc5\u8981\u3060\u3002<br>Astronomy is especially important to sailors.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>2. \u5148\u307b\u3069\u304b\u3089\u6b8a\u306b\u76ee\u3092\u60f9\u3044\u305f\u4e00\u4eba\u306e\u7537\u6027\u304c\u3044\u305f\u3002<br>There was one person from earlier who particularly drew my attention.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>3. \u96ea\u5d29\u306e\u8de1\u3067\u9053\u304c\u6b8a\u306b\u60aa\u304f\u306a\u3063\u3066\u3044\u305f\u3002<br>The road had become especially worse by what the avalanche left behind.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In older language, \u6b8a\u306b could also mean &#8220;moreover.&#8221;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>4.\u00a0\u6b8a\u306b\u3053\u306e\u9803\u306f\u897f\u5c71\u3001\u6771\u5c71\u306e\u82b1\u76db\u308a\u306b\u3066\u3042\u308b\u3068\u7533\u3057\u3066<br>Moreover, (they) say that the Nishiyama and Higashiyama are in full bloom at this time.<br>From \u300e\u733f\u5ea7\u982d\u300f by \u864e\u6e05\u72c2<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">\u7279\u306b &amp; \u7279\u5225\uff08\u306b\uff09<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The adverb&nbsp;\u7279\u306b also means &#8220;especially\/particularly&#8221; by indicating that something stands out as being different than the norm, but unlike \u6b8a\u306b it can also refer to &#8220;special\/preferential&#8221; treatment.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>5. \u4eca\u65e5\u306f\u3010\u7279\u306b\u30fb\u7279\u5225\uff08\u306b\uff09\u3011\u6691\u3044\u3002<br>Today is particularly hot.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>6.&nbsp;&nbsp;\u767a\u5c55\u9014\u4e0a\u56fd\u3067\u96c7\u7528\u304c\u7279\u306b\u60aa\u5316\u3057\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3002<br>Employment is particularly worsening in developing countries.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>7. \u300c\u4f55\u304b\u554f\u984c\u304c\u3042\u3063\u305f\uff1f\u300d\u300c\u7279\u306b\u306a\u3044\u3088\u300d<br>&#8220;Where there any problems?&#8221; &#8220;There weren&#8217;t any in particular.&#8221;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u7279\u5225\uff08\u306b\uff09 can also be used as an adverb, indicating that the state or disposition of something surpasses other things. It also shares \u7279\u306b&#8217;s meaning of referring to &#8220;special\/preferential&#8221; treatment. You will also see \u7279\u5225 used as an adjectival noun to mean &#8220;special\/particular.&#8221; As an adjectival noun, it usually takes \u306a, but it is also very common to find it in compound words.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>8.\u00a0\u5728\u7559\u3092\u7279\u5225\u306b\u8a31\u53ef\u3059\u308b\u3002<br>To especially allow for (someone) residing.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>9. \u7279\u5225\u306a\u3082\u306e\u306a\u3093\u3066\u8981\u3089\u306a\u3044\u3002<br>I don&#8217;t need anything special.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>10. \u6f22\u691c\u306f\u81ea\u5206\u306b\u306f\u7279\u5225\u5fc5\u8981\u306a\u3044\u3068\u601d\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u5b66\u751f\u304c\u3044\u308b\u304b\u3082\u3057\u308c\u307e\u305b\u3093\u3002<br>There may be students who think that the Kanken is not particularly important to themselves.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>11.&nbsp; \u7279\u5225\u6599\u91d1\u3067\u7533\u8fbc\u53d7\u4ed8\u4e2d\uff01<br>Accepting subscriptions at a special (lower) rate!&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">\u683c\u5225\uff08\u306b\uff09&amp; \u683c\u6bb5\u306b<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>\u683c\u5225\uff08\u306b\uff09is also very similar to \u7279\u5225\uff08\u306b\uff09in that it marks an exceptionally true quality. It can also have the nuance of being &#8220;especially selected\/treated with exception.&#8221;&nbsp;The difference in nuance between it and&nbsp;\u7279\u5225 is that it&nbsp;indicates that something is especially better.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Just like \u7279\u5225, \u683c\u5225 may also be used as an adjectival noun meaning &#8220;special\/particular,&#8221; and as an adjectival noun, it usually takes the particle \u306e.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>12. \u51ac\u306f\u934b\u304c\u683c\u5225\u306b\u7f8e\u5473\u3057\u3044\u5b63\u7bc0\u3067\u3059\u306d\uff01<br>Winter is the season when hot pot tastes especially delicious.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>13. \u96e8\u306e\u65e5\u306f\u683c\u5225\u3068\u3057\u3066\u3001\u6bce\u65e5\u30b8\u30e0\u306b\u884c\u304d\u306a\u3055\u3044\u3002<br>With exception to rainy days, go to the gym daily.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>14. \u5e73\u7d20\u306f\u683c\u5225\u306e\u304a\u5f15\u304d\u7acb\u3066\u3092\u8cdc\u308a\u3001\u539a\u304f\u5fa1\u793c\u7533\u3057\u4e0a\u3052\u307e\u3059\u3002<br>I wish to express my deep gratitude for the substantial support you always provide.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u683c\u6bb5\u306b is particularly closely related to the word \u683c\u5225\uff08\u306b\uff09, but rather than indicating that something is far better than something else, its nuance indicates that the difference at hand is a&nbsp;&#8220;marked\/noticeable&#8221; one at that. The difference is also usually a positive one.&nbsp;When it is used as an adjectival noun, it usually takes the particle \u306e.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>15. \u4e00\u822c\u306e\u4eba\u3068\u6280\u91cf\u306b\u683c\u6bb5\u306e\u9055\u3044\u304c\u3042\u308b\u3002<br>There is a substantial difference in skill between (him) and ordinary people.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>16. \u79c1\u304b\u3089\u8a00\u308f\u305b\u308b\u3068\u683c\u6bb5\u306b\u4e0a\u9054\u3057\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3068\u611f\u3058\u3066\u304a\u308a\u307e\u3059\u3002<br>If you ask me, I feel that (he) has markedly improved.<br><br>If you want to say that something is at a wildly different level than something, you can also use the synonym \u6bb5\u9055\u3044\u306b. As an adjectival noun, it can take \u306a or \u306e.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>17. \u30d5\u30a1\u30a4\u30bf\u30fc\u306e\u5f37\u3055\u3082\u6bb5\u9055\u3044\u3060\u3002<br>The fighter&#8217;s strength is on another level.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>18. \u30c0\u30f3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\u3067\u51fa\u73fe\u3059\u308b\u4ed6\u306e\u30e2\u30f3\u30b9\u30bf\u30fc\u3088\u308a\u6bb5\u9055\u3044\u306b\u5f37\u3044\u30e2\u30f3\u30b9\u30bf\u30fc\u304c\u51fa\u73fe\u3059\u308b\u3002<br>Monsters wildly stronger than other monsters that appear in dungeons will appear.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">\u3068\u308a\u308f\u3051\uff08\u3066\uff09<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Deriving from the te-form of the verb \u53d6\u308a\u5206\u3051\u308b meaning &#8220;to distribute\/divide,&#8221;\u3068\u308a\u308f\u3051\uff08\u3066\uff09 means &#8220;especially,&#8221; but it is preferred in&nbsp;objective contexts and is not used in relation to actions that are done purposefully or willfully.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>19. \u4eca\u5e74\u306f\u3068\u308a\u308f\u3051\u96e8\u304c\u591a\u3044\u3002<br>This year has especially had a lot of rain.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>20. \u3068\u308a\u308f\u3051\u653f\u6cbb\u754c\u306b\u304a\u3044\u3066\u306f\u5fc5\u305a\u3068\u8a00\u3063\u3066\u3044\u3044\u307b\u3069\u6539\u9769\u306f\u632b\u6298\u3059\u308b\u3002<br>Especially in the world of politics, it is safe to say that reformation will invariably fail.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>21.&nbsp;\u4e16\u754c\u4e2d\u304c\u3042\u306a\u305f\u306e\u7269\u306b\u306a\u3063\u3066\u3044\u3066\u3082\u53d6\u308a\u5206\u3051\u3066\u672c\u56fd\u3092\u304a\u611b\u3057\u306a\u3055\u3044\u3002<br>Even if the whole world becomes yours, love thy home country above all.From \u300e\u30d5\u30a1\u30a6\u30b9\u30c8\u300fby \u68ee\u9dd7\u5916.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Variation Note<\/strong>: \u3068\u308a\u308f\u3051\u3066 is identical in meaning and usage to \u3068\u308a\u308f\u3051, but it is usually only encountered in writing.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u3068\u308a\u308f\u3051 can best be understood as pinpointing what is&nbsp;&#8220;especially so among others.&#8221; In this sense, it may be used to refer to personal opinion or the action of others, making it&nbsp;interchangeable with \u7279\u306b, but it maintains its objective lens on the situation.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>22.\u30b9\u30dd\u30fc\u30c4\u306e\u4e2d\u3067\u306f\u3010\u3068\u308a\u308f\u3051\u30fb\u7279\u306b\u3011\u30b5\u30c3\u30ab\u30fc\u304c\u597d\u304d\u3067\u3059\u3002<br>Among sports, I especially like soccer.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>23. \u3068\u308a\u308f\u3051\u30dc\u30af\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u3092\u71b1\u5fc3\u306b\u3084\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3002<br>(Among other things, he) is especially patient about boxing.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Orthography Note<\/strong>: The kanji spelling of \u3068\u308a\u308f\u3051 is \u53d6\u308a\u5206\u3051, but it is seldom used.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">\u5c31\u4e2d<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>\u306a\u304b\u3093\u305a\u304f, also more traditionally spelled as&nbsp;\u306a\u304b\u3093\u3065\u304f, is a contraction of \u306a\u304b\u306b\u3064\u304f and means &#8220;especially&#8230; among other things&#8221; and is a more literary, fancy synonym to the second usage of \u3068\u308a\u308f\u3051.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>24. \u3059\u3079\u3066\u306e\u5b66\u79d1\u306b\u8a00\u3048\u308b\u304c\u3001\u306a\u304b\u3093\u305a\u304f\u56fd\u8a9e\u304c\u91cd\u8981\u3067\u3042\u308b\u3002<br>Though the same can be said for every subject, Japanese language instruction is especially important.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>25. \u305f\u3060\u9053\u306f\u6700\u3082\u5965\u3067\u3001\u5c71\u306f\u5c31\u4e2d\u6df1\u3044\u304c\u3001\u6803\u6728\u5ce0\u304b\u3089\u4e2d\u306e\u6cb3\u5185\u306f\u8d8a\u305b\u305d\u3046\u3067\u3042\u308b\u3002<br>The road is simply further deep with the mountains being especially deep, but Kawachi, in its interior, seems passable from Tochigi Pass.<br>From \u300e\u6803\u306e\u5b9f\u300fby \u6cc9\u93e1\u82b1.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">\u5225\u306b &amp; \u5225\u6bb5<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Although all these adverbs can be used in negative sentences, the two&nbsp;synonyms that can only be used in negative structures are \u5225\u306b and&nbsp;\u5225\u6bb5. Both words&nbsp;mean &#8220;not particularly\/especially,&#8221; the latter form being more literary.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>26. \u305d\u3053\u3082\u5225\u6bb5\u5909\u308f\u3063\u305f\u6240\u3082\u306a\u304b\u3063\u305f\u3002<br>There wasn&#8217;t anything particularly unusual there either.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>27. \u5f7c\u306f\u5225\u6bb5\u3001\u6226\u4e89\u306b\u5354\u529b\u3059\u308b\u3088\u3046\u306a\u4e00\u884c\u306e\u717d\u52d5\u7684\u306a\u6587\u7ae0\u3092\u66f8\u3044\u3066\u306f\u3044\u306a\u3044\u3002<br>He hasn&#8217;t particularly written any&nbsp;incendiary passage abetting war.&nbsp;<br>From\u300e\u901a\u4fd7\u3068\u5909\u8c8c\u3068\u300fby&nbsp;\u5742\u53e3\u5b89\u543e.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>28. \u79d1\u5b66\u306f\u5225\u306b\u7279\u5225\u306a\u77e5\u8b58\u3067\u306f\u306a\u304f\u3066\u3001\u7d50\u5c40\u306f\u77e5\u8b58\u305d\u306e\u3082\u306e\u306b\u3059\u304e\u306a\u3044\u3002<br>Science isn&#8217;t especially particular knowledge but ultimately knowledge itself and nothing more.&nbsp;<br>From \u300e\u79d1\u5b66\u7de8\u300f by \u6238\u5742\u6f64.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">\u6b8a\u66f4 VS \u308f\u3056\u3068 VS \u6545\u610f\u306b<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>\u6b8a\u66f4 has two meanings, one of which is meaning &#8220;particularly&#8221; as the emphatic version of \u6b8a\u66f4.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>29. \u5584\u3068\u304b\u60aa\u3068\u304b\u3044\u3046\u3053\u3068\u304c\u4f55\u3067\u3042\u308b\u304b\u306f\u4eca\u6b8a\u66f4\u554f\u984c\u306b\u3057\u307e\u3044\u3002<br>I will not particularly make issue of what exactly &#8220;good&#8221; and &#8220;evil&#8221; are now.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>30.&nbsp;&nbsp;\u305d\u306e\u7a2e\u306e\u7b11\u3044\u8a71\u306f\u672c\u96c6\u306b\u3082\u6975\u3081\u3066\u591a\u3044\u304c\u3001\u6b8a\u66f4\u306b\u591a\u304f\u3092\u96c6\u3081\u305f\u306e\u3067\u306f\u306a\u3044\u3002<br>There is an extremely large amount of such funny stories in this compilation, but it isn&#8217;t that (we) have particularly collected lots of them.&nbsp;<br>From \u300e\u4e2d\u56fd\u7b11\u8a71\u96c6\u300f by \u99d2\u7530\u4fe1\u4e8c.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The second meaning of \u6b8a\u66f4 is indicating &#8220;intentional\/deliberate&#8221; action. In negative contexts, it may give off the meaning of &#8220;not particularly necessary to&#8221; which could be viewed the same as saying &#8220;no need to go out of one&#8217;s way to.&#8221;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In positive contexts such as Ex. 26, you can actually see how the &#8220;intentional&#8221; meaning derives from its use to &#8220;particularly&#8221; be a certain way but in a transitive context.&nbsp;<br><br><strong>Particle Note<\/strong>: For this second usage, you may also see the particle \u306b with no change in meaning or nuance.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>31. \u7b4b\u8089\u306f\u6b8a\u66f4\uff08\u306b\uff09\u81a8\u8139\u3057\u3001\u7537\u3089\u3057\u3055\u3092\u5f37\u8abf\u3059\u308b\u3002<br>His muscles especially swelled up (on purpose), emphasizing his manliness.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>32. \u6b8a\u66f4\uff08\u306b\uff09\u8ab0\u306b\u8074\u304b\u305b\u3088\u3046\u3068\u3057\u3066\u6b4c\u3063\u3066\u3044\u305f\u3082\u306e\u3067\u306f\u306a\u3044\u3002<br>(I) wasn&#8217;t singing that to intentionally have someone listen to it.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>A far more common way to say &#8220;deliberately\/on purpose,&#8221; though, is \u308f\u3056\u3068.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>33. \u55ab\u8336\u5ba4\u306b\u30e9\u30d5\u30a1\u30a8\u30eb\u541b\u304c\u3044\u308b\u3053\u3068\u306b\u306f\u6c17\u3065\u3044\u3066\u3044\u305f\u304c\u3001\u308f\u3056\u3068\u8996\u7dda\u3092\u5408\u308f\u305b\u306a\u304b\u3063\u305f\u3002<br>Although I had noticed that Rafael was in the coffee room, I purposely made sure I eyes didn&#8217;t meet.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>34. \u4eba\u306e\u524d\u3067\u308f\u3056\u3068\u3053\u3093\u306a\u3053\u3068\u3092\u3057\u3066\u898b\u305b\u305f\u304c\u308b\u5973\u304c\u3044\u308b\u306a\u3093\u3066\u30fb\u30fb\u30fb<br>To think there&#8217;d be a woman who would purposely want to show off doing this sort of thing in front of people&#8230;<br><br><strong>Orthography Note<\/strong>: The kanji spelling of \u308f\u3056\u3068 is \u614b\u3068, but it is seldom used.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In technical speech, the adverb \u6545\u610f\u306b will also be seen.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>35. \u305f\u3068\u3048\u3070\u4ed6\u4eba\u304c\u305d\u306e\u6adb\u3067\u982d\u3092\u68b3\u304b\u3057\u305f\u3053\u3068\u306f\u306a\u304b\u3063\u305f\u304b\u3002\u3042\u308b\u3044\u306f\u6545\u610f\u306bA\u578b\u306e\u4eba\u306e\u6bdb\u3092\u305d\u3053\u306b\u5165\u308c\u3066\u88c1\u5224\u6240\u306b\u63d0\u51fa\u3057\u306a\u304b\u3063\u305f\u304b\u3002<br>For instance, are you sure another person didn&#8217;t use a comb on the person&#8217;s head? Are you sure no one deliberately placed hair of an A-type individual there and then presented that to the court?\u00a0<br>From \u300e\u6b7b\u4f53\u306f\u8a9e\u308b\u300fby \u4e0a\u91ce\u6b63\u5f66.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>36. \u72af\u4eba\u306f\u6b7b\u4f53\u306e\u907a\u68c4\u3092\u6545\u610f\u306b\u8150\u98df\u52d5\u7269\u306b\u4efb\u305b\u305f\u53ef\u80fd\u6027\u304c\u51fa\u3066\u304d\u305f\u306e\u3067\u3042\u308b\u3002<br>The strong possibility has arisen that the criminal abandoned the body and purposefully left it for scavengers.&nbsp;<br>From \u300e\u866b\u9001\u308a\u300f by \u548c\u7530\u306f\u3064\u5b50.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Adverbs for &#8220;Especially&#8221;: \u6b8a\u306b, \u7279\u306b,&nbsp;\u5c31\u4e2d, \u3068\u308a\u308f\u3051, \u6b8a\u66f4, etc. This lesson focuses on an array of inter<a class=\"more-link\" href=\"https:\/\/imabi.org\/adverbs-for-especially\/\">\u7d9a\u304d\u3092\u8aad\u3080 <span class=\"screen-reader-text\">&#8220;Adverbs for &#8220;Especially&#8221;&#8221;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":158153075,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"advanced_seo_description":"","jetpack_seo_html_title":"","jetpack_seo_noindex":false,"jetpack_post_was_ever_published":false,"footnotes":""},"tags":[],"class_list":["post-979","page","type-page","status-publish","hentry"],"jetpack_likes_enabled":true,"jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/PeXUlI-fN","jetpack-related-posts":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/imabi.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/979","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/imabi.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/imabi.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/imabi.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/158153075"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/imabi.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=979"}],"version-history":[{"count":3,"href":"https:\/\/imabi.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/979\/revisions"}],"predeces